  "elapsed_s": 4.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] That they're basically a religious people, that they believe in God, and that one of their main activities was especially among a very big elderly population were to read their Bibles and-- and pray to God.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And what was-- that they had one culture, in many respect much superior than the culture of these villages where they were transported.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And their behave, was one behave of very high morals.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So they-- and besides that, they had very many remembrances of when this persecution was not existing, when this-- many of these people were leading intellectuals, writers.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, my uncle is the only one Bulgarian writer that received Nobel Prize.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "The greatest musicians were also of Jewish descendance.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, one of them, Pancho Vladigerov, was the nephew of one of the very great Russian writers, Boris Pasternak, the author of He have some of his work dedicated to his grandfather, Leonid Pasternak, that was actually the father of Boris Pasternak.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Presently [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] his name is the title name of the-- the National Academy of Music, National Academy of Music now appears the name of Pancho Vladigerov.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He was one very, very great talent, and teaching of many, many of the most gifted Bulgarian musicians, one of which was the very famous pianist Alexis Weissenberg, a worldly famous pianist, his pupil of piano.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "He also was my teacher of theory.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "I-- much later on, received also from his son, one dedication.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "He wishes that during my lifetime that I make a recording of all his works that he composed for violin and piano, something that I carried in my heart for many, many years, and hope one day to happen.",
      "word_count": 39
    }
  ],
